<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g524719g84j41.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>From the Independent Members of Tesla&#146;s Board of Directors </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Fellow Tesla Stockholders, </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We continue to have great optimism for Tesla&#146;s future as we implement our mission of accelerating the world&#146;s transition to
sustainable energy &#151; a mission that is both critical to our planet and has the potential to create significant value for Tesla stockholders. To keep Tesla moving forward on this path, Elon and the rest of the team must have the right incentives
in place to lead us there. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">When we went public in 2010, we were a relatively small company with only one product &#151; the
Tesla Roadster, a high-priced and low-volume electric sports car. Since that time, we have developed a range of sustainable energy products, including electric vehicles that are not only the world&#146;s highest-performing cars, but also the safest
and among the top-selling in their categories. We have also grown our annual revenue by about 100x and our market capitalization by almost 35x, from about $1.6 billion to over $55 billion. We are proud of what the company has achieved and the
significant value that has been created for all of our stockholders. But there is much more to be done. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As you know, we are
more than a car company. We are the world&#146;s first vertically integrated sustainable energy company, with a wide variety of products, from generation to storage to consumption. As we described in Master Plan, Part Deux, the next phase of our
development involves a number of exciting plans that will further accelerate the inevitable shift toward a sustainable energy future. These include expanding solar energy generation through Solar Roof and other solar products and seamlessly
integrating them with battery storage, building out our vehicle product line to cover all major forms of terrestrial transport, continuing to advance autonomous technology to create a fully-self driving future, and enabling sharing so that your car
can make money for you when you are not using it. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As Tesla continues to grow, we have created a new 10-year performance award
for Elon that incentivizes him to not only continue to lead Tesla over the long-term, but to help the company achieve these great goals. You will find more details about the proposed award in the following pages, but the basic premise is simple
&#151; <I>Elon&#146;s compensation will be 100% aligned with the interests of our stockholders.</I> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Elon will receive no
guaranteed compensation of any kind &#151; no salary, no cash bonuses, and no equity that vests by the passage of time. Instead, Elon&#146;s only compensation will be a 100% at-risk performance award, which ensures that he will be compensated only
if Tesla and all of our stockholders do extraordinarily well. The award consists of stock options that vest only if Tesla achieves specific milestones, which if fully achieved would make Tesla one of the most valuable companies in the world with a
market capitalization of at least $650&nbsp;billion&nbsp;&#151; more than 10x today&#146;s value. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In crafting this award, we
were mindful of Elon&#146;s existing stock ownership levels and the strong belief that the best outcome for our stockholders is for Elon to continue leading the company over the long-term. We created the award after more than six months of careful
analysis with a leading independent compensation consultant as well as discussions with Elon, who along with Kimbal otherwise recused themselves from the Board process. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Importantly, we modeled this performance award on the prior performance award that Elon received in 2012. We believe his prior award was instrumental in helping Tesla achieve the objectives laid out in
the original Tesla Master Plan and the tremendous stockholder value that was created as a result. In just the five years after that award was put in place, our market capitalization has increased 17x. By linking Elon&#146;s compensation entirely to
Tesla&#146;s performance so that he does not receive any compensation unless all our stockholders benefit from significant value creation, the new performance award will similarly ensure that Elon and the team are totally aligned with stockholder
interests going forward. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We believe Tesla has a unique opportunity to continue delivering stockholder value. Our
aspirations may appear ambitious to some, and impossible to others, and that is by design. We like setting challenging, hard-to-achieve goals for ourselves, and then focusing our efforts to make them happen. This is why we based this new award on
stretch goals and why we gave Elon the ability to share in the upside in a way that is commensurate with the difficulty of achieving them. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you are a stockholder of record or beneficial owner of Tesla as of the Record Date, which is February&nbsp;7, 2018, you will be entitled to vote your shares. Elon and Kimbal will recuse themselves from
the vote, which means that other Tesla stockholders such as you will determine its outcome and the future course of Tesla. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We recommend that you vote &#147;FOR&#148; the proposed CEO Performance Award. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sincerely, </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Antonio J. Gracias (Lead Independent Director) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Ira Ehrenpreis (Chair of the Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors) </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Brad W. Buss </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Robyn M. Denholm </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Linda Johnson Rice </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">James Murdoch </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>NOTICE OF SPECIAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>TO BE HELD ON MARCH&nbsp;21, 2018 </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Tesla Stockholders: </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We would like to notify you of a special meeting of
stockholders, which will be held at the Tesla Training Center facility, located at 45201 Fremont Boulevard, Fremont, California 94538 on March&nbsp;21, 2018 at 9:00 a.m., Pacific Time (the &#147;<U>Special Meeting</U>&#148;). The only item on the
agenda of the Special Meeting will be to consider and vote on a proposal to approve the grant of a stock option award (the &#147;<U>CEO Performance Award</U>&#148;) to Elon Musk, Tesla&#146;s Chief Executive Officer and Chairman, as described in
more detail in this proxy statement. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On January&nbsp;21, 2018, the Board of Directors of Tesla (the
&#147;<U>Board</U>&#148;), with Elon Musk and Kimbal Musk recusing themselves, (1)&nbsp;determined that the grant of the CEO Performance Award is fair to, advisable and in the best interests of Tesla and its stockholders, (2)&nbsp;approved the grant
of the CEO Performance Award, and (3)&nbsp;resolved to recommend that Tesla stockholders vote for the approval of the CEO Performance Award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends that Tesla stockholders vote &#147;FOR&#148; the CEO Performance Award. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Tesla will transact no other business at the Special Meeting except such business as may properly be brought before the Special Meeting or any adjournment or postponement thereof. Please note that Elon
will recuse himself from attending any forum at which decisions regarding the CEO Performance Award are made, at both the Board and stockholder levels. Accordingly, Elon will not be present at the Special Meeting, nor will there be a Tesla
presentation or questions and answers session as in past meetings of stockholders. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Approval of the CEO Performance Award
requires (1)&nbsp;the affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the total votes of shares of Tesla common stock cast in person or by proxy at the Special Meeting, pursuant to the rules of The Nasdaq Stock Market LLC (the &#147;<U>NASDAQ Stock
Market Rules</U>&#148;), (2)&nbsp;the affirmative vote of a majority of the voting power of the shares present in person or represented by proxy at the Special Meeting and entitled to vote on the proposal, pursuant to Tesla&#146;s amended and
restated bylaws, and (3)&nbsp;the affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the total votes of shares of Tesla common stock not owned, directly or indirectly, by Elon Musk or Kimbal Musk, cast in person or by proxy at the Special Meeting,
pursuant to the resolutions of the Board approving the CEO Performance Award. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All stockholders as of the close of business
on February&nbsp;7, 2018 may attend the Special Meeting in person. <B>If you intend to attend the Special Meeting in person, please read this proxy statement carefully to ensure that you have proper evidence of stock ownership as of February&nbsp;7,
2018, as we will not be able to accommodate guests without such evidence at the Special Meeting.</B> </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Your vote is very
important. Whether or not you plan to attend the Special Meeting, we encourage you to read the proxy statement and vote as soon as possible. For specific instructions on how to vote your shares, please refer to the section entitled
&#147;</B><B><I>Questions and Answers About the Special Meeting and Procedural Matters</I></B><B>&#148; and the instructions on your proxy card or the voting instruction card you receive from your broker, bank or other intermediary. Please note that
if you hold shares in different accounts, it is important that you vote the shares represented by each account. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you
have any questions concerning the CEO Performance Award or this proxy statement, would like additional copies of this proxy statement or need help voting your shares of Tesla common stock, please contact Tesla&#146;s proxy solicitor: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Innisfree M&amp;A Incorporated </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">501 Madison Avenue </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New York, NY 10022 </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Stockholders Call Toll Free: (877)&nbsp;456-3463 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">International Callers: &#43;1 (412)&nbsp;232-3651 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Thank you for your ongoing
support of Tesla. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:52%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Board of Directors of Tesla, Inc. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The date of this proxy statement is February&nbsp;8, 2018 and it is being mailed to stockholders on or about February&nbsp;12, 2018.
</FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I><A HREF="#toc524719_21">Equity Compensation Award Information</A></I></FONT></P></TD>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">i </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>TESLA, INC. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>3500 Deer Creek Road </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Palo Alto, California 94304 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PROXY STATEMENT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>FOR SPECIAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>TO BE HELD ON MARCH&nbsp;21,
2018 </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc524719_1"></A>CAUTIONARY STATEMENT REGARDING FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This proxy statement contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995.
Statements in this proxy statement that are not historical facts are hereby identified as &#147;forward-looking statements&#148; for the purpose of the safe harbor provided by Section&nbsp;21E of the Exchange Act, and Section&nbsp;27A of the
Securities Act. These forward-looking statements, including, without limitation, those relating to possible future market prices, market capitalization levels for Tesla common stock and Tesla&#146;s results of operations, wherever they occur in this
proxy statement, are necessarily estimates reflecting the best judgment of the management of Tesla and involve a number of risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from those suggested by the forward-looking
statements. These forward-looking statements should, therefore, be considered in light of various important factors, including those set forth in this proxy statement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Words such as &#147;estimate,&#148; &#147;project,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;intend,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;anticipate,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148; &#147;would,&#148; &#147;should,&#148;
&#147;could&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements are found at various places throughout this proxy statement. Important factors that could cause actual results to differ
materially from those indicated by such forward-looking statements include those set forth in Tesla&#146;s filings with the SEC, including its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 and Quarterly Report on Form
10-Q for the fiscal quarter ended September&nbsp;30, 2017. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Tesla undertakes no obligation to publicly update any
forward-looking statement, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise. In the event that Tesla does update any forward-looking statement, no inference should be made that Tesla will make additional updates with respect to
that statement, related matters or any other forward-looking statements. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc524719_2"></A>CEO PERFORMANCE AWARD PROPOSAL </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc524719_3"></A>Executive Summary </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Since its IPO in 2010, Tesla has gone from having just a tiny number of cars on the road to about 300,000, it has grown revenue about 100x, and it has created significant value for its stockholders, with
its market capitalization having increased almost 35x. Most importantly, Tesla is a mission-driven company, devoted to accelerating the world&#146;s transition to sustainable energy, and it has made important strides towards this goal. However,
Tesla&#146;s Board of Directors (the &#147;<U>Board</U>&#148;) believes that there is much more to be done. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As Tesla embarks
on the next phase of its development, it is no longer just a small automobile manufacturer. It is now the world&#146;s only vertically integrated sustainable energy company, with products ranging from generation to storage to consumption, and the
Board believes that it is on a path that, with proper execution, could result in Tesla becoming one of the most valuable companies in the world. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">With that goal in mind, the Board is asking Tesla&#146;s stockholders to approve a 10-year performance award for Mr.&nbsp;Musk that will incentivize his continued leadership of Tesla over the long-term.
This award is fully aligned with Tesla&#146;s long-term ambitions and the interests of its stockholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2012,
Tesla&#146;s Board approved a performance stock option award for Mr.&nbsp;Musk that required Tesla to grow its market capitalization in $4 billion increments from what was then less than a $4 billion company to a company that is now worth more than
$55 billion, and to concurrently execute 10 key operational goals. Although these milestones were viewed at the time as very difficult to achieve, by last year, all of the market capitalization milestones had been achieved, and all but one of the
operational milestones have now been achieved as well. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Early in 2017, with the 2012 Performance Award heading to substantial
completion, the independent members of the Board began preliminary discussions about how to continue to incentivize Mr.&nbsp;Musk to lead Tesla through the next phase of its development. Through more than six months of work and with the help of a
third-party compensation consultant, the CEO Performance Award was developed. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under the CEO Performance Award, which is
attached as <U>Appendix A</U>, Mr. Musk will receive no salary, no cash bonuses, and no equity that vests simply by the passage of time. Instead, his only compensation will be a 100% at-risk performance award, consisting exclusively of stock options
with tranches that vest only if one market capitalization milestone and one operational milestone are both achieved. For the first tranche, Tesla&#146;s current market capitalization has to increase to $100 billion and the Company must meet an
additional operational milestone. For each subsequent tranche, Tesla must increase its market capitalization in additional $50 billion increments&#151;up to a total of $650 billion&#151;and achieve another previously unmet operational milestone at
each level. The award consists of a 10-year grant of stock options with 12 potential vesting tranches, and is designed to help ensure that Tesla is executing well on both a top-line and bottom-line basis. For each tranche that is achieved, Mr. Musk
will vest in a number of stock options that corresponds to approximately 1% of Tesla&#146;s current total outstanding shares. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;Musk must also remain as Tesla&#146;s CEO or serve as both Executive Chairman and Chief Product Officer, in each case with all
leadership ultimately reporting to him, at the time each milestone is met in order for the corresponding tranche to vest. This ensures Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s active leadership of Tesla over the long-term while also providing the flexibility to bring
in another CEO who would report to Mr.&nbsp;Musk at some point in the future. Although there is no current intention for this to happen, it provides flexibility as Tesla continues to grow to potentially allow Mr.&nbsp;Musk to focus more of his
attention on the kinds of key product and strategic matters that most impact Tesla&#146;s long-term growth and profitability. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Board&#146;s primary objective in designing the CEO Performance Award is to help Tesla
grow and achieve its mission, which would facilitate the creation of significant stockholder value. There are three main reasons why the Board recommends that stockholders approve the award. The CEO Performance Award: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Strengthens Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s incentives and further aligns his interests with those of Tesla&#146;s other stockholders; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Ensures Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s continued leadership of Tesla over the long-term; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Serves as a catalyst for the achievement of Tesla&#146;s strategic and financial objectives, which include growing Tesla into one of the most valuable and successful
companies in the world and further accelerating the inevitable shift toward a sustainable energy future. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc524719_4">
</A>Background of the CEO Performance Award </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Board created a new 10-year performance award for Mr.&nbsp;Musk, who
is Tesla&#146;s Chief Executive Officer and Chairman. He is also a substantial stockholder of Tesla, and beneficially owned as of December&nbsp;31, 2017, an aggregate of 37,853,041 shares of Tesla common stock. See the section entitled &#147;<I>CEO
Performance Award Proposal &#151; Potential Ownership of Securities</I><I> As a Result of the CEO Performance Award</I>&#148; on page&nbsp;<B></B>18<B></B> for more information. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2012, the Board approved a compensation program for Mr.&nbsp;Musk that consisted entirely of performance stock options that would vest
only upon the achievement of certain market capitalization and operational milestones (the &#147;<U>2012 Performance Award</U>&#148;). At the time, Tesla had begun to execute on the original Master Plan that laid out the objectives for Tesla during
the first phase of its development. It had yet to begin volume production of Model S and had a market capitalization of under $4 billion. The vesting milestones for the 2012 Performance Award included 10 tranches, with each tranche requiring Tesla
both to (i)&nbsp;grow market capitalization by an additional $4 billion, and (ii)&nbsp;achieve an additional specified operational milestone. Following the grant of the 2012 Performance Award, Tesla received strong stockholder support in its
triennial &#147;Say on Pay&#148; votes in 2014 and 2017 (94.4% and 98.9%, respectively, of the shares present or represented by proxy and entitled to vote). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Since 2012, Tesla has, among other things, (a)&nbsp;launched and ramped up production of Model S, which is the top-selling car in its segment in many key markets around the world, (b)&nbsp;designed,
launched and ramped up production of Model X, which continues to gain substantial market share, (c)&nbsp;designed, launched and started to ramp up production of Model 3, a mass-market vehicle that the success of Model S and Model X enabled and which
has already been reserved by hundreds of thousands of customers, and (d)&nbsp;added important new business lines, including solar energy generation and energy storage. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the five years since the 2012 Performance Award was put in place, Tesla&#146;s market
capitalization has increased 17x. The Board believes that the 2012 Performance Award played a significant role in Tesla&#146;s operational and financial success by properly aligning Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s incentives with the best interests of Tesla
and its stockholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g524719g81c00.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">With the 2012 Performance Award nearing completion, the Board engaged in more than six months of
active and ongoing discussions regarding a new compensation program for Mr.&nbsp;Musk, ultimately concluding in its decision to grant the CEO Performance Award. These discussions first took place among the members of the Compensation Committee of
the Board (the &#147;<U>Compensation Committee</U>&#148;), all of whom are independent directors, and then with the Board&#146;s other independent directors, including its two newest independent directors, Linda Johnson Rice and James Murdoch.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">These discussions extensively covered each of the various considerations that were involved in deciding to grant the CEO
Performance Award, including, among other things: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(i)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The reasons for an award; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(ii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The desire to incentivize and motivate Mr.&nbsp;Musk to continue to lead Tesla over the long-term and to create significant stockholder value in doing so;
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">How to structure an award in a way that would further align the interests of Mr.&nbsp;Musk and Tesla&#146;s other stockholders; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iv)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Whether to model an award based on elements of the 2012 Performance Award; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(v)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">What performance milestones should be used in an award; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(vi)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">What the total size of an award should be and how that size would translate into increased ownership and value for Mr.&nbsp;Musk; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">How to balance the risks and rewards of a new award. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For each of the relevant Compensation Committee and Board meetings, both Elon Musk and
Kimbal Musk recused themselves. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Throughout this process, the Board used the services of Compensia, which served as its
independent compensation consultant, and Wilson Sonsini Goodrich&nbsp;&amp; Rosati, P.C. (&#147;<U>WSGR</U>&#148;), which served as its special outside counsel. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At various points during this process, the independent members of the Board met with Mr.&nbsp;Musk to share their thinking on the award and get his perspective, including as to each of the issues
identified above and ultimately to negotiate the terms of the award with him. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Additionally, early in the Board&#146;s
process, at the request of the Compensation Committee, Ira Ehrenpreis and Tesla&#146;s General Counsel, Todd Maron, had calls with 15 of Tesla&#146;s largest institutional stockholders to discuss and solicit their views regarding the 2012
Performance Award and considerations for a new compensation award for Mr.&nbsp;Musk, in light of the fact that nearly all of the milestones in the 2012 Performance Award had been or would be achieved in the near future. Many of these stockholders
indicated that they favored the approach used in the 2012 Performance Award, especially when coupled with Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s lack of traditional non-performance based types of compensation (i.e., no salary, no cash bonuses, no time-based equity
awards), and indicated that they favored a new equity award to Mr.&nbsp;Musk broadly based on the model of the 2012 Performance Award that would motivate and incentivize his continued service and dedication to Tesla. Stockholders suggested various
operational milestones to pair with market capitalization milestones, but in general expressed preferences for financial-based operational milestones that would ensure both top-line and bottom-line Tesla growth as a condition for awards of
compensation to Mr.&nbsp;Musk. As the Board thereafter deliberated on a new performance award for Mr. Musk, it gave great weight to the feedback that its stockholders provided during these calls, and it incorporated much of that feedback into the
ultimate design of the award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">After engaging in this extended process and arriving at terms for a performance award to which
both the independent members of the Board and Mr.&nbsp;Musk agreed, and concluding that such an award would motivate and incentivize Mr.&nbsp;Musk to continue to lead the management of Tesla over the long-term, the Board, with Elon Musk and Kimbal
Musk recusing themselves, granted the CEO Performance Award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:2%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>The Master Plan and 2012 Performance Award History
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2006, Mr.&nbsp;Musk published the original Tesla Master Plan in which he laid out a vision for Tesla that started with
building electric sports cars and then leveraged that into a broad product base of affordable cars and zero emission electric power generation options. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Prior to option grant awards made in December 2009, Mr.&nbsp;Musk did not receive any equity compensation for his services for a period of five years. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2010 and 2011, Mr.&nbsp;Musk did not receive any equity grants, because the Compensation Committee believed his existing grants made
in December 2009 already provided sufficient motivation for Mr.&nbsp;Musk to perform his duties as Chief Executive Officer. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2012, to create incentives for continued long-term success from the Model S program as well as from Tesla&#146;s planned Model X and
Model 3 programs, and to further align executive compensation with increases in stockholder value, the Compensation Committee reviewed Mr.&nbsp;Musk&#146;s equity compensation and retained Compensia as its outside compensation consultant to advise
it in doing so. Following such review, the Compensation Committee recommended to the Board that a new stock option grant be made to Mr.&nbsp;Musk. On August&nbsp;1, 2012, the Board approved the 2012 Performance Award, which consisted of a grant to
Mr.&nbsp;Musk of options to purchase 5,274,901 shares of Tesla&#146;s common stock at an exercise price of $31.17 per share, representing 5% of Tesla&#146;s total issued and outstanding shares as of August&nbsp;13, 2012, the effective date of such
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">5 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
grant. The 2012 Performance Award consisted of 10 equal vesting tranches, with a vesting schedule based entirely on the attainment of both operational and market capitalization milestones, as
further detailed below. The 2012 Performance Award was designed to be an incentive for future performance that would take many years to achieve, if at all, and was a 100% at-risk performance award. Mr.&nbsp;Musk and the Board viewed the milestones
as very challenging at the time the Board granted the 2012 Performance Award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under the 2012 Performance Award, each of the
10 vesting tranches requires that Tesla meet a combination of (i)&nbsp;an operational milestone achievement and (ii)&nbsp;a $4 billion increase in Tesla&#146;s market capitalization. Consequently, the 2012 Performance Award would fully vest only if
Tesla achieved a sustained market capitalization increase from $3.2 billion to $43.2 billion, and all 10 operational milestones described were achieved. Market capitalization for purposes of milestone achievement was determined based on a rolling
six&nbsp;month historic average (based on trading days only). The market capitalization for a particular trading day is equal to the closing price multiplied by the outstanding shares of common stock as of the end of such trading day. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The 10 operational milestones for the 2012 Performance Award are: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

believes that the 2012 Performance Award was instrumental in helping Tesla achieve the objectives that were laid out in the original Tesla Master Plan, along with the tremendous stockholder value that was created during the process. </FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Market Capitalization
Milestones</U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a.&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;12 Market Capitalization Milestones</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">b.&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;First tranche
milestone is a market capitalization of $100 billion; each tranche thereafter requires an additional $50 billion in market capitalization to vest, up to $650 billion market capitalization for the last tranche</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">c.&#8195;&#8201;&#8202;Sustained market capitalization is required for each Market Capitalization Milestone to be met, other than in a change in control situation. Specifically, there are two prongs that
must be met to achieve a given Market Capitalization Milestone:</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:6.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Six calendar month trailing average (based on trading days); and</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:6.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;30 calendar day trailing average (based on trading days).</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Operational Milestones</U></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a.&#8195;&#8194;&#8202;16 Operational
Milestones, of which up to 12 may be paired with Market Capitalization Milestones for all tranches to vest</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">b.&#8195;&#8194;Two types of Operational Milestones:</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:-0.80em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Eight&nbsp;focused&nbsp;on&nbsp;revenue:</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Eight&nbsp;focused&nbsp;on&nbsp;profitability:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Total&nbsp;Revenue*</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" ALIGN="center"><FONT

stockholders before (ii) interest expense, (iii) (benefit) provision for income taxes, (iv) depreciation and amortization, and (v) stock-based compensation, as each such item is reported in our financial statements on Forms 10-Q or 10-K filed with

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="14%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="5%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="5%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="20%"></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B><U>Award Terms</U></B></FONT>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="9" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B><U>Details</U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Vesting</U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Each of the 12 tranches vests only when both a Market Capitalization Milestone and an Operational Milestone are certified by the Board as having been
met.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Any one of the 16 Operational Milestones can be
matched with any one of the 12&nbsp;Market Capitalization Milestones, but any single Operational Milestone may only satisfy the vesting requirement for one tranche.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A Market Capitalization Milestone and an Operational Milestone
that are matched together can be achieved at different points in time and vesting will occur at the later of the achievement certification dates for such Market Capitalization Milestone and Operational Milestone. Subject to any applicable clawback
provisions, policies or other forfeiture terms, once a milestone is achieved, it is forever deemed achieved for determining the vesting of a tranche.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0.60em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Term of CEO Performance Award</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">10 years</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Post-Termination of
Employment Exercise Period</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">One year</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Post-Exercise Holding
Period</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Five years, to further align Mr.
Musk&#146;s interests with Tesla stockholders&#146; interests following option exercise.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Employment Requirement For Continued
Vesting</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Vesting eligibility contingent
upon being:</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1.&#8195;&#8194;Chief
Executive Officer; or</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2.&#8195;&#8194;Executive Chairman and Chief Product Officer.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Extended exercise period</U>: If Mr. Musk is still employed
at Tesla in a role other than the specified roles above, he will no longer be able to vest under the CEO Performance Award but can continue to hold unexercised vested options for the full term of the CEO Performance Award.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Termination of
Employment</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">No acceleration of vesting upon
termination of employment, death or disability.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Change in Control of Tesla</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">No automatic acceleration of
vesting upon a change in control of Tesla, but in a change in control situation the achievement of the milestones will be based solely on the Market Capitalization Milestones, measured at the time of such change in control without regard to the six
calendar month and 30 calendar day trailing averages of Tesla&#146;s stock price. In other words, upon a change in control where Tesla is acquired, vesting of milestones under the CEO Performance Award does not require the achievement of a matching
Operational Milestone.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The treatment of the CEO
Performance Award upon a change in control is intended to align Mr. Musk&#146;s interests with Tesla&#146;s other stockholders with respect to evaluating potential takeover offers.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.60em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exercise Methods / Requirements</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="9" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Exercise Methods:</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1.&#8195;&#8194;Cashless: sufficient shares
to cover exercise prices and taxes are simultaneously sold upon exercise of options; and</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2.&#8195;&#8194;Cash: exercise price is paid in cash upon exercise of options.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">10 </FONT></P>



<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>
